    "discriminators": [
     "A body hitting the ground is the most heavily DAMPED impact in the taxonomy: flesh has terrible acoustic impedance and dissipates the strike as heat, so there is essentially no ring. Low centroid, LF-dominated, very short decay, dull. Those four together are a real, measurable morphology.",
     "Against FIGHT-IMPACT (a punch): a bodyfall is BIGGER and LONGER — the whole mass lands, usually with a scuffle or a slide afterwards, so transient_count is higher and the tail is messier. A punch is one compact thud. A lean, not a boundary.",
     "Against WOOD-IMPACT / METAL-IMPACT: those RING. If decay_time_seconds_60db is long or the spectrum is bright and inharmonic, it is not a body. That direction of the test is reliable."
    ],
