    "discriminators": [
     "Cloth is a high-centroid, noisy, LOW-CREST friction texture with no f0 and almost no low-band energy — the antithesis of the impacts around it. It SUSTAINS rather than spiking, so crest_factor is low and sustain_ratio well above zero. Separable from FIGHT-IMPACT and FIGHT-BODYFALL on centroid and crest alone.",
     "Against FOLEY-CLOTH and CLOTH-MOVEMENT: physically identical. The only difference UCS states is INTENSITY — 'active or big scuffling cloth' — so expect higher level, higher spectral_flux and more violent envelope modulation than a walking foley pass. A soft lean, not a boundary, and that is what caps this at narrowable."
    ],
