    "discriminators": [
     "A hand seizing an arm: a brief cloth-and-skin friction gesture, often with a soft impact at the front. It is a HYBRID of FIGHT-CLOTH (the friction) and FIGHT-IMPACT (the slap of contact) and sits between them with no clean boundary on either side.",
     "UCS folds arm BLOCKS in here as well ('similar sounds'), which blurs it further against FIGHT-IMPACT. Against FOLEY-HANDS the physics is identical.",
     "Honestly semantic_only: nothing in the signal says 'grapple'. The gates exist only to rule out blasts, rings and tonal material."
    ],
