    "discriminators": [
     "A punch or kick landing on a body: a compact, DAMPED, front-loaded thud. The defining feature is what is ABSENT — there is no ring. decay_time_seconds_60db is tiny and high_band_energy is low, because flesh absorbs rather than resonates.",
     "Against FIGHT-BODYFALL: a punch is a single small compact impact; a bodyfall is bigger and longer, with more low-band mass and usually a scuffle afterwards. Real but weak.",
     "Against GORE-SPLAT and GORE-SQUISH: the same damped body impact, only WET — gore adds mid-band burble and a messier tail. The dry/wet axis is the only lean and it is not a boundary.",
     "Against METAL-IMPACT / WOOD-IMPACT: if it rings, it is not a body. That rules OUT reliably; it never rules IN."
    ],
